  "body": "Rationale: expose and promote descriptor wallets in more places; make cli tool more consistent with `createwallet` rpc.\r\n\r\nAdd `-descriptors` parameter which is off by default. When specified it will create a new descriptors wallet with sqlite backend, which is consistent with `createwallet` rpc.\r\n\r\nThis PR is based on a suggestion from **ryanofsky** https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/19137#discussion_r516779603\r\n\r\nExample:\r\n```\r\n$ ./src/bitcoin-wallet  -wallet=fewty -descriptors create\r\nTopping up keypool...\r\nWallet info\r\n===========\r\nName: fewty\r\nFormat: sqlite\r\nDescriptors: yes\r\nEncrypted: no\r\nHD (hd seed available): yes\r\nKeypool Size: 6000\r\nTransactions: 0\r\nAddress Book: 0\r\n```\r\n```\r\n$ ./src/bitcoin-wallet  -wallet=fewty create\r\nTopping up keypool...\r\nWallet info\r\n===========\r\nName: fewty\r\nFormat: bdb\r\nDescriptors: no\r\nEncrypted: no\r\nHD (hd seed available): yes\r\nKeypool Size: 2000\r\nTransactions: 0\r\nAddress Book: 0\r\n```",
